s they discover how learning English can transform their lives. With humor, emotion, and a touch of documentary style, the series culminates in a final project that inspires not only the characters but everyone to take the first step toward a brighter future through language learning.","original_language":"en","directors":["Gustavo Fernando","Maria Eduarda Silva do Nascimento"],"cast":["Gustavo Fernando","Maria Eduarda Silva do Nascimento","Yasmim da Silva Melo","Gracielly Vitória","Thiago Luis dos Santos"],"slug":"tafers-code"},{"id":1418397,"title":"Anchorless","release_date":"2026-12-05","poster_path":"/qZsROZuYSMT4nCTuuaskNrSa6Cw.jpg","backdrop_path":"/bMgYrjasQPJkHayXWLmdolijTEt.jpg","vote_average":0,"vote_count":0,"genre_ids":[18,10749],"overview":"During a trip to Brazil in 2022, Augusto (15), an introspective and dreamy young man, becomes enchanted by Antônio (16), a magnetic and unpredictable boy from Belém. Amid the heat of the World Cup and the waters reflecting a fleeting encounter, a fragile connection is born, stretching across distance when Augusto returns to Italy, turning desire into obsession. While Augusto loses himself in idealizations and the emptiness of delayed responses, Antônio continues his life between parties, friends, and fleeting loves. What begins as a promising romance crumbles under the weight of time, silence, and the things that were never said. As the years pass, Augusto is forced to face an inevitable truth: some loves do not belong to the future, they exist only in memory. An intimate and visceral portrait of love, loss, and growth, Anchorless delves into the fragility of first feelings and the pain of learning that not every story is destined to last.","original_language":"pt","directors":["Murillo Campos"],"cast":["Alice Braga","Sofia Cordeiro","Bia Jordão","Graciely Junqueira"],"slug":"anchorless"},{"id":1003596,"title":"Avengers: Doomsday","release_date":"2026-12-17","poster_path":"/s2Fkuq0tj7mjAHEdbfQkFkdbeRI.jpg","backdrop